```

Now we define the basic counting operations:

```tactics
/-- The length of a walk is the number of edges/darts along it. -/
def length {u v : V} : G.LoopWalk u v → ℕ
  | nil => 0
  | cons _ q => q.length.succ
  | loop q => q.length.succ
```

The length of a loop walk is defined recursively. A `nil` walk has length 0. A `cons` walk adds 1 (via `succ`) to the length of the remaining walk. A `loop` walk also adds 1 to the length of the remaining walk.

Next, we define the `support` of a walk, which is the list of vertices it visits:

```tactics
/-- The `support` of a walk is the list of vertices it visits in order. -/
def support {u v : V} : G.LoopWalk u v → List V
  | nil => [u]
  | cons _ p => u :: p.support
  | loop p => u::p.support
```

The support of a loop walk is also defined recursively. The support of `nil` is `[u]` (the starting vertex). The support of `cons h p` is `u` (the starting vertex of this step) followed by the support of `p`. The support of `loop p` is `u` (the starting vertex of the loop) followed by the support of `p`.

Next, we define `supportSet` as the finset of vertices visited:

```tactics
/-- The `supportSet` of a LoopWalk is the set of vertices it visits.-/
