Therefore, the sum `∑ e ∈ edgeSet (cons h p), edgeCount (cons h p) e` is equal to `∑ e ∈ (edgeSet p) ∪ {Sym2.mk (u, v)}, edgeCount (cons h p) e`.

Since `edgeCount (cons h p) e` is `edgeCount p e` if `e ∈ edgeSet p`, and `edgeCount p (Sym2.mk (u, v)) + 1` if `e = Sym2.mk (u, v)`.

