The edges of `cons h p` are `(Sym2.mk (u, v)) ++ edges p`.

Therefore, `count (· = e) (edges (cons h p))` is `count (· = e) (edges p)` if `e ≠ Sym2.mk (u, v)`, and `count (· = e) (edges p) + 1` if `e = Sym2.mk (u, v)`.

