We need to prove `∑ e ∈ edgeSet (loop p), edgeCount (loop p) e = (loop p).length`.

The induction hypothesis is `∑ e ∈ edgeSet p, edgeCount p e = p.length`.

The length of `loop p` is `p.length + 1`.

The edge set of `loop p` is the edge set of `p` union the edge corresponding to the loop. But since `p` is a loop walk from `u` to `v`, its last step is `v`. The loop adds an edge from `v` back to `u`. So the edge set of `loop p` is `(edgeSet p) ∪ {Sym2.mk (u, v)}`.

