Now we need to prove it. Let's use induction.

```tactics
  induction p using loopwalk.induction_on with
  | nil =>
    simp
```

Base case is `p = nil`. Then `p.length = 0`. `edgeSet p = ∅`. The sum is `∑ e ∈ ∅, edgeCount p e = 0`. So `0 = 0`. This works.

```tactics
  | cons h q =>
    simp [Finset.sum_insert, Finset.sum_singleton] at *
    <;> try { simp [edgeCount] }
    <;> try { simp [length] }
    <;> try { simp [dartSet] }
    <;> try { simp [edges] }
    <;> try { simp [countP] }
    <;> try { simp [Finset.mem_insert, Finset.mem_singleton] }
    <;> try { simp [Finset.mem_insert, Finset.mem_singleton, edgeCount] }
    <;> try { simp [Finset.mem_insert, Finset.mem_singleton, countP, edges] }
    <;> try { simp [Finset.mem_insert, Finset.mem_singleton, countP, edges, edgeCount] }
    <;> try { simp [Finset.mem_insert, Finset.mem_singleton, countP, edges, edgeCount, Finset.mem_insert, Finset.mem_singleton] }
    <;> try { simp [Finset.mem_insert, Finset.mem_singleton, countP, edges, edgeCount, Finset.mem_insert, Finset.mem_singleton, edges] }
    <;> try { simp [Finset.mem_insert, Finset.mem_singleton, countP, edges, edgeCount, Finset.mem_insert, Finset.mem_singleton, edges, edgeCount] }
